Syntax:
	<command> [<value>] - set all displays
	<command> <index=[value]> [<index=[value]> ...] - set specific displays
	
Commands:
	gamma - set display gamma
	brightness - set display brightness
	
Index:
	1 is first connected display
	2 is second connected display
	etc...
	
Value:
	brightness: decimal, e.g. 0.3 (default is 1.0 if unspecified)
	gamma: decimal or triplet (e.g. 0.3:0.5:0.8 as R:G:B)
	
Install to $PATH (e.g. /usr/bin on Arch) to allow easy access via shell or DE run bar

Requires:
	xrandr
	bash 4+
	gnu coreutils (grep, cut, sort)
